author: The Current
description:
Jeff Tweedy and his solo tour bandmates talk about what they call him
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

In September, Wilco frontman Jeff Tweedy released his solo triple album, "Twilight Override." Tweedy and his band visited The Current studio to play songs from the album and then to talk with host Jessica Paxton. In a band lineup featuring his own children and neighbors, the question is posed about what people in the band call Jeff Tweedy when talking to him. To paraphrase Shakespeare, that which they call a bandleader by any other name would sound as sweet. 

Jeff Tweedy’s 2025 album, "Twilight Override," is available on dBpm Records.

Musicians
Jeff Tweedy – vocals and guitar
Sammy Tweedy – vocals and keyboards / synths
Spencer Tweedy – drums
Sima Cunningham – bass and vocals
Liam Kazar – guitar and vocals 
Macie Stewart – violin and vocals

Credits
Guest – Jeff Tweedy
Host – Jessica Paxton
Producer – Derrick Stevens
Video – Aaron Ankru
title: Do Jeff Tweedy's solo tour bandmates call him "Dad," "Jeff" or "Mr. Tweedy"? #shorts #family
